verblex: 1. Of behaviour, to be unkind and unpleasant. English = (be) nasty, (be) mean.
2. To be very unpleasant to see, experience or feel. English = (be) nasty.
3. To complain or talk about something or someone in a nasty way. English = bitch
nomlex: 1. Behaviour which is unkind and unpleasant. English = nastiness.
2. Someone who behaves in a very unpleasant way. English = bitch.
